Oh, is your daughter sick?

537
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:06,812
I'm not sick.

538
00:20:07,177 --> 00:20:08,252
Can we please go?

539
00:20:08,267 --> 00:20:13,512
Kelley finds suddenly she has a need
for these products.

540
00:20:13,527 --> 00:20:18,670
And, uh, and we were hoping you might
show her how to use them.

541
00:20:26,567 --> 00:20:28,270
George, you're married.

542
00:20:28,466 --> 00:20:30,350
You should be happy.
You don't look happy.

543
00:20:30,377 --> 00:20:31,702
I'm sick, Olivia.

544
00:20:32,176 --> 00:20:33,391
All right, you could...

545
00:20:33,475 --> 00:20:34,740
uh, you should go home, O'Malley.

546
00:20:34,825 --> 00:20:36,642
Clearly whatever you have is contagious.

547
00:20:38,648 --> 00:20:39,553
Aren't you from the lab?

548
00:20:39,586 --> 00:20:41,070
Yeah, I feel like crap.

549
00:20:41,146 --> 00:20:43,521
Is that the lady you gave,
uh, Marina's blood to?

550
00:20:43,657 --> 00:20:45,231
Uh, yeah.

551
00:20:45,255 --> 00:20:46,841
And you all feel shaky and nauseous?

552
00:20:46,906 --> 00:20:47,692
It's awful.

553
00:20:49,785 --> 00:20:50,861
She's toxic.

554
00:20:50,908 --> 00:20:51,620
Callie? Yeah.

555
00:20:51,686 --> 00:20:52,693
A lot of us feel that way.

556
00:20:52,705 --> 00:20:54,333
No, the patient's blood is toxic.

557
00:20:54,418 --> 00:20:55,333
It's making us sick.

558
00:20:56,008 --> 00:20:58,521
Has the chief started, uh,
Marina's operation?

559
00:20:58,547 --> 00:21:00,940
They were wheeling her up
as I came down.

560
00:21:01,337 --> 00:21:02,820
What's the extension for O.R. One?

561
00:21:13,727 --> 00:21:16,432
The patient's blood is apparently highly
toxic. Any contact is dangerous.

562
00:21:16,448 --> 00:21:18,732
Nobody goes in there until we figure
out what the hell is going on.

563
00:21:18,745 --> 00:21:19,473
How's he doing?

564
00:21:20,138 --> 00:21:22,532
He's tachypneic, but his B.P.
Is starting to stabilize.

565
00:21:22,547 --> 00:21:23,672
He's doing better on oxygen.

566
00:21:23,686 --> 00:21:25,390
It's a good thing he got
out of there when he did.

567
00:21:25,408 --> 00:21:26,253
- Yeah.
- Dr. Shepherd.

568
00:21:26,288 --> 00:21:27,403
- What is it?
- Can you sign this?

569
00:21:27,417 --> 00:21:28,930
I just heard. How can I help?

570
00:21:28,995 --> 00:21:30,130
You're off duty.
You should be with your mother.

571
00:21:30,155 --> 00:21:31,490
I don't want to spend time
with my mother.

572
00:21:31,506 --> 00:21:33,551
The chief is down. Alex is down.
I would like to help.

573
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:34,170
Dr. Grey...

574
00:21:34,965 --> 00:21:36,102
you want to help?
Talk to your resident.

575
00:21:39,398 --> 00:21:40,102
What do you got?

576
00:21:40,187 --> 00:21:42,223
They found an herbal supplement
in her purse.

577
00:21:42,227 --> 00:21:44,963
The lab guys think it combined
with the chemo chemicals

578
00:21:44,977 --> 00:21:46,883
and turned her blood into some
kind of neurotoxin.

579
00:21:46,888 --> 00:21:48,161
We're lucky they're not all dead.

580
00:21:48,175 --> 00:21:50,011
The only reason she's alive
is because she's intubated.

581
00:21:50,048 --> 00:21:50,860
Who got them out of there?

582
00:21:50,868 --> 00:21:51,441
O'Malley.

583
00:21:53,726 --> 00:21:54,383
George.

584
00:21:54,397 --> 00:21:56,163
Callie, she was toxic.

585
00:21:56,217 --> 00:21:58,811
Her blood was toxic, not our marriage.

586
00:21:58,868 --> 00:22:00,011
You thought our marriage was toxic?

587
00:22:00,907 --> 00:22:02,632
Okay, all our people are being treated.

588
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:03,880
Now what do we do about her?

589
00:22:09,805 --> 00:22:10,442
Dr. Grey,

590
00:22:10,955 --> 00:22:15,131
your holter monitor shows you're having
multiple runs of tachycardia every hour,

591
00:22:15,157 --> 00:22:17,283
so Dr. Burke would like
to do a radioablation.

592
00:22:17,338 --> 00:22:20,181
Why would he recommend surgery when
medication can keep it under control?

593
00:22:23,988 --> 00:22:26,662
Because Alzheimer's patients aren't
always compliant with their meds.

594
00:22:26,716 --> 00:22:29,691
And apparently, Meredith says...

595
00:22:30,885 --> 00:22:32,481
you are particularly difficult.

596
00:22:36,415 --> 00:22:38,121
I could elect not to treat it at all.

597
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:40,950
Your stress test shows coronary
artery disease.

598
00:22:41,285 --> 00:22:42,870
That coupled with the tachyarrhythmia

599
00:22:42,885 --> 00:22:44,653
could cause too much stress on your
heart, which would

600
00:22:45,857 --> 00:22:46,771
eventually...

601
00:22:52,575 --> 00:22:53,451
what would you do

602
00:22:54,537 --> 00:22:57,332
if the thing that defines who you are

603
00:22:58,976 --> 00:22:59,841
was taken away?

604
00:23:05,905 --> 00:23:06,920
Tell Dr. Burke...

605
00:23:10,006 --> 00:23:11,271
I don't want the surgery.

606
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:12,112
I'm...

607
00:23:12,816 --> 00:23:16,033
I'm s... I'm very sorry, Dr. Grey,
but technically, that

608
00:23:16,656 --> 00:23:18,123
decision isn't yours.

609
00:23:18,696 --> 00:23:19,533
It's Meredith's.

610
00:23:21,705 --> 00:23:23,941
This is a maxi pad... heavy flow day.

611
00:23:23,977 --> 00:23:27,951
Mini pad... pretty self-explanatory...
just peel the label and stick it.

612
00:23:28,395 --> 00:23:29,890
And the tampon we've already gone over.
So

613
00:23:30,645 --> 00:23:31,742
are we clear on everything?

614
00:23:34,846 --> 00:23:35,290
Kelley...

615
00:23:36,315 --> 00:23:37,103
I understand

616
00:23:37,227 --> 00:23:39,552
that you're a little mortified that your
dad dragged you in here,

617
00:23:39,565 --> 00:23:42,542
but can you just talk or nod
or something?

618
00:23:42,676 --> 00:23:43,821
I get it, okay?

619
00:23:44,466 --> 00:23:46,411
How's it going with our very
first patient?

620
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:47,473
Kelley's a woman.

621
00:23:47,636 --> 00:23:50,512
Can I just go to the gallery and learn
something, if that's okay with you?

622
00:23:50,728 --> 00:23:51,223
Okay.

623
00:23:56,588 --> 00:23:59,821
Uh, Mr. Hanson, if you could go to the
front desk and fill out some paperwork,

624
00:23:59,865 --> 00:24:00,540
 I can get you outta here.

625
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:04,072
Of course, of course.
Uh... thank you.

626
00:24:04,346 --> 00:24:09,501
Since my wife died, I... I've been in
the woods a little with Kelley.

627
00:24:10,266 --> 00:24:10,600
Okay.

628
00:24:10,705 --> 00:24:11,020
Yeah.

629
00:24:15,255 --> 00:24:18,020
Are you okay, Kelley? Any cramps?
'Cause a heating pad...

630
00:24:18,035 --> 00:24:19,651
Could I be pregnant if I had sex last
week ? 

631
00:24:19,698 --> 00:24:22,001
Like, before the period thing started?
'Cause I did,

632
00:24:22,108 --> 00:24:26,543
and it would really suck if I was pregnant
'cause now the guy's being a real jerk,
and he's totally ignoring me at school.

633
00:24:27,495 --> 00:24:30,423
So I really hope I can't be pregnant.
I can't, right?

634
00:24:33,837 --> 00:24:36,282
Any way you could, like, answer me
before my dad gets back?

635
00:24:37,757 --> 00:24:40,340
I'm not sure refusing treatment
is what you want to do.

636
00:24:40,345 --> 00:24:44,010
Apparently what I want doesn't matter.
It isn't even legally binding.

637
00:24:44,976 --> 00:24:47,613
So it's really about what you want,
Meredith. You're in charge.

638
00:24:47,646 --> 00:24:50,372
You think I like making
these decisions for you?

639
00:24:50,535 --> 00:24:52,941
Do you think it's fun to get
calls from the nursing home

640
00:24:52,998 --> 00:24:55,222
asking whether I was planning
on giving the nurse

641
00:24:55,306 --> 00:24:57,631
who changes you every morning
a Christmas tip?

642
00:24:57,886 --> 00:25:02,430
But I do it, because you have managed
to alienate everybody else in your life.

643
00:25:02,568 --> 00:25:04,751
And I am the only one,

644
00:25:05,277 --> 00:25:07,033
so I have to step up and do it.

645
00:25:08,606 --> 00:25:11,420
You want to know why I'm so unfocused,

646
00:25:12,756 --> 00:25:13,940
so ordinary?

647
00:25:15,417 --> 00:25:17,000
You want to know what happened to me?

648
00:25:17,146 --> 00:25:19,040
You. You happened to me.

649
00:25:19,065 --> 00:25:20,911
- Then let me refuse the heart surgery.
- No.

650
00:25:21,028 --> 00:25:22,933
- Why not?
- Because killing my mother

651
00:25:23,728 --> 00:25:26,351
is not gonna be another thing
that happens to me.

652
00:25:31,398 --> 00:25:32,811
These suits are airtight.

653
00:25:32,837 --> 00:25:35,330
These packs recirculate the air
trapped inside.

654
00:25:35,995 --> 00:25:37,510
These batteries haven't been
charging long.

655
00:25:37,526 --> 00:25:40,470
I'm guessing you got about 30 minutes
before they die and you have to come out.

656
00:25:40,645 --> 00:25:43,093
Oh, my god. The anesthesia's
wearing off. She's waking up.

657
00:25:44,595 --> 00:25:45,953
30 minutes starting now.

658
00:25:45,967 --> 00:25:47,232
She's fighting intubation.

659
00:25:47,248 --> 00:25:49,342
We go inside before
these seals are secure,

660
00:25:49,478 --> 00:25:51,260
we wouldn't last five minutes,
and she will die.

661
00:25:51,308 --> 00:25:52,580
These guys are two minutes out.

662
00:25:52,746 --> 00:25:54,603
- She doesn't have two minutes.
- Addison!

663
00:26:03,445 --> 00:26:04,532
Get the hell outta there!

664
00:26:04,547 --> 00:26:07,200
She's awake, Mark. She's awake
and open on the table.

665
00:26:07,217 --> 00:26:09,720
I need to know her weight so I can
dose her with the propofol.

666
00:26:09,976 --> 00:26:12,013
She looks about 60 kilos.

667
00:26:14,935 --> 00:26:15,661
you're okay.

668
00:26:16,975 --> 00:26:17,572
It's okay.

669
00:26:18,236 --> 00:26:18,712
Got it.

670
00:26:24,885 --> 00:26:26,471
I got you. I got you. It's okay.

671
00:26:38,057 --> 00:26:39,183
Looks like S.V.T.

672
00:26:40,298 --> 00:26:41,930
Push 10 of adenosine
and page Dr. Burke.

673
00:26:41,948 --> 00:26:44,122
He's already gone into surgery.
I'll get the adenosine.

674
00:26:46,076 --> 00:26:48,431
Carotid massage.
Carotid massage.

675
00:26:48,727 --> 00:26:53,093
Carotid massage can reboot the heart
and stop the S.V.T. Okay, okay, hold on.

676
00:26:54,375 --> 00:26:56,103
Oh, hold on, please. Hold on, please.

677
00:27:01,488 --> 00:27:03,092
Hold on. Hold on.

678
00:27:05,367 --> 00:27:05,941
Okay.

679
00:27:06,836 --> 00:27:08,410
Okay, okay, okay, okay.

680
00:27:08,476 --> 00:27:08,810
oh.

681
00:27:23,585 --> 00:27:24,211
You're good.

682
00:27:25,095 --> 00:27:26,393
Sharp under pressure.

683
00:27:27,347 --> 00:27:28,981
You'll make an extraordinary surgeon.

684
00:27:38,628 --> 00:27:40,682
Dr. Grey, I need to ask you...

685
00:27:42,336 --> 00:27:43,501
will it get in my way?

686
00:27:45,057 --> 00:27:46,131
Can I have both?

687
00:27:46,668 --> 00:27:48,683
Can I be a great surgeon
and have a life?

688
00:27:48,716 --> 00:27:51,202
Because there is this man
who just asked me to marry him,

689
00:27:51,236 --> 00:27:52,682
and I know you tried to have both,

690
00:27:52,826 --> 00:27:54,381
but you split up with
Meredith's dad and...

691
00:27:56,068 --> 00:27:59,221
- I know this is none of my business.
- It is none of your business.

692
00:28:06,487 --> 00:28:07,922
And I didn't try hard enough.

693
00:28:11,498 --> 00:28:12,143
Thank you.

694
00:28:23,955 --> 00:28:24,892
Are you feeling better?

695
00:28:25,847 --> 00:28:28,902
Oh, I will be once my patient's
off the table.

696
00:28:29,527 --> 00:28:30,213
Look at these two...

697
00:28:31,028 --> 00:28:34,751
a heart surgeon and a neurosurgeon
performing a bowel resection.

698
00:28:34,967 --> 00:28:36,520
You think the world stops when you stop,

699
00:28:37,608 --> 00:28:38,793
but it keeps on going.

700
00:28:42,745 --> 00:28:45,173
People perform your surgeries
better than you could.

701
00:28:45,498 --> 00:28:47,372
The next generation comes up, and

702
00:28:48,446 --> 00:28:49,991
you're scared you'll be forgotten.

703
00:28:53,555 --> 00:28:55,141
Your mother stopped for five years,

704
00:28:56,217 --> 00:28:57,440
and you became someone.

705
00:28:58,778 --> 00:29:00,092
According to her, I didn't.

706
00:29:00,947 --> 00:29:02,872
According to her, I'm a disappointment.

707
00:29:04,145 --> 00:29:07,251
Well, in a perfect world she'd be able
to tell you she was proud of you.

708
00:29:07,557 --> 00:29:08,803
But it's not a perfect world,

709
00:29:11,138 --> 00:29:12,673
and your mother's not a perfect woman.

710
00:29:18,087 --> 00:29:20,982
I think the person she'd most like to
see right now is you.

711
00:29:26,556 --> 00:29:30,063
The only thing your mother wants to hear
from me is that I regret staying with Adele.

712
00:29:31,048 --> 00:29:32,662
That's the only gift I could give her.

713
00:29:34,655 --> 00:29:35,662
And I can't tell her that.

714
00:29:38,048 --> 00:29:38,732
That's not true.

715
00:29:54,685 --> 00:29:55,871
They won't fit.

716
00:29:58,837 --> 00:29:59,813
Stop right there.

717
00:30:00,385 --> 00:30:02,190
The bowel swelled.
You won't have any room.

718
00:30:02,527 --> 00:30:04,541
- How much time do you have?
- Eight minutes.

719
00:30:06,047 --> 00:30:06,420
Okay,

720
00:30:07,325 --> 00:30:08,290
now listen to me

721
00:30:08,716 --> 00:30:10,002
and do everything I say.

722
00:30:10,298 --> 00:30:14,443
Kelley, your pregnancy test is negative,
and you're clean for S.T.D.S.

723
00:30:14,485 --> 00:30:15,502
- Oh, thank god.
- Great.

724
00:30:15,776 --> 00:30:17,570
Thanks to you, I'm also grounded
for the rest of my life.

725
00:30:18,038 --> 00:30:19,002
Kelley, be polite.

726
00:30:19,128 --> 00:30:22,550
I'm sorry, Sir, but polite doesn't seem
to be getting you two very far.

727
00:30:25,305 --> 00:30:28,830
Kelley, your dad told me you lost your
mother a few years ago,

728
00:30:29,008 --> 00:30:33,903
and I want to say how sorry I am. You
probably have a million of questions.

729
00:30:34,125 --> 00:30:35,252
And if your mother were here,

730
00:30:35,296 --> 00:30:38,753
I'm sure she would have more eloquent
answers than I do.

731
00:30:38,796 --> 00:30:42,243
But I think that she and I would
actually be saying the same thing,

732
00:30:42,327 --> 00:30:46,603
which is if you keep going
the way you're going,

733
00:30:46,966 --> 00:30:51,123
you will get an S.T.D.,
You will get pregnant,

734
00:30:51,238 --> 00:30:55,040
you will increase your chances
of getting cervical cancer.

735
00:30:57,087 --> 00:30:58,321
You're not being smart.

736
00:30:59,375 --> 00:31:02,662
And you're too young for anyone to
expect you to be smart

737
00:31:02,768 --> 00:31:06,083
the way you need to be
when you're having sex,

738
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:08,533
which means you shouldn't be having it.

739
00:31:11,606 --> 00:31:13,621
I thought he liked me.

740
00:31:13,888 --> 00:31:17,100
Oh. Oh, honey, I know you did.

741
00:31:19,388 --> 00:31:20,653
I know you did.

742
00:31:34,867 --> 00:31:36,130
okay, you're gonna live.

743
00:31:36,697 --> 00:31:37,640
Callie, wait.

744
00:31:38,187 --> 00:31:40,082
I was a little bit heroic in there.

745
00:31:40,445 --> 00:31:40,772
Mm.

746
00:31:41,458 --> 00:31:42,421
I thought you'd be proud of me.

747
00:31:42,456 --> 00:31:45,383
Proud? You were poisoned, and you
thought it was about me.

748
00:31:45,387 --> 00:31:47,861
- It felt like an anxiety attack.
- About me.

749
00:31:48,315 --> 00:31:53,453
You see, we...we were fine when we
were in our Vegas bubble, when it was
just room service and pay cable and us,

750
00:31:53,517 --> 00:31:56,852
it was bliss, but then you get around
your weird and judgy friends for one day

751
00:31:56,987 --> 00:32:00,641
and suddenly you're racked with
uncertainty, toxic-gas-level uncertainty.

752
00:32:01,165 --> 00:32:03,231
I guess it was too much to hope
you'd just stand up for me.

753
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:05,231
- Cal
- and middle name is Iphegenia.

754
00:32:06,416 --> 00:32:07,013
Okay?

755
00:32:07,427 --> 00:32:09,700
I can't wait to hear what your pals
have to say about that.

756
00:32:24,495 --> 00:32:27,632
So that was pretty cool, what you just
did. Going in and putting her back under.

757
00:32:27,665 --> 00:32:29,311
Cool or stupid...

758
00:32:30,436 --> 00:32:31,202
Take your pick.

759
00:32:33,015 --> 00:32:33,542
Huh.

760
00:32:37,496 --> 00:32:38,203
Okay.

761
00:32:38,446 --> 00:32:39,730
All right. I gotta...

762
00:32:41,395 --> 00:32:42,003
go.

763
00:32:48,838 --> 00:32:49,443
What's going on?

764
00:32:49,745 --> 00:32:53,460
The chief figured out the anesthesiologist
didn't have time to drop an N.G. Tube.

765
00:32:53,577 --> 00:32:55,851
So now they have to place one
and decompress

766
00:32:55,898 --> 00:32:57,933
and repack her intestines and close.

767
00:32:57,975 --> 00:32:59,940
And they're about to run out of air.

768
00:33:01,117 --> 00:33:01,763
Holy crap.

769
00:33:02,656 --> 00:33:04,290
This so beats tampon training.

770
00:33:04,518 --> 00:33:08,403
Preston, you'll need to milk the bowel
to get out the excess fluid.

771
00:33:09,015 --> 00:33:11,301
Pack her and wrap her and get
her stable for transport.

772
00:33:11,535 --> 00:33:13,510
- How's Georges?
- Medically he's fine.

773
00:33:13,636 --> 00:33:15,593
Emotionally? He's a little
stunted if you ask me.

774
00:33:15,606 --> 00:33:17,960
You don't marry the rebound girl.
Am I right?

775
00:33:17,996 --> 00:33:19,411
You don't marry anyone on a whim.

776
00:33:19,435 --> 00:33:21,803
- Well, he needs our support.
- He doesn't need us.

777
00:33:22,005 --> 00:33:23,531
He's got his Vegas show-wife.

778
00:33:23,908 --> 00:33:24,202
Oh.

779
00:33:24,668 --> 00:33:27,183
Chief, they're at 32 minutes.
You gotta pull'em out.

780
00:33:28,026 --> 00:33:29,070
How you doin' on air?

781
00:33:34,428 --> 00:33:35,752
- I'm out.
- You go.

782
00:33:36,965 --> 00:33:38,380
- I'll wrap it.
- Alone?

783
00:33:40,296 --> 00:33:41,030
